17... Qc7
{ The start of Black's plan of putting the queen on b6 to protect the knight on c5 and then Black can play ...d6-d5. }
18. Nf2 Rfe8 19. Kh1 Qb6 20. Qc2 d5
{ This is the problem with White's plan with Nf2 and e4, Black comes first. }
21. cxd5 cxd5 22. Nxd5 Nxd5 23. Bxc5 Qc7
{ White didn't manage to find compensation for the weaknesses in his position and soon lost in Gelfand-Kamsky, Tashkent 2012. }
