9... Bxe6 10. Bf4
{ An innocent line where Black can equalize in multiple ways. } 10... Bxc4 11.
Qxd6 { The start of a forcing sequence. } 11... Qxd6 12. Bxd6 Re8 13. Ne5 Be6
14. Rac1 Nbd7
{ Black has no problems. Long-term, it might be easier for us to combine putting pressure on the b2-pawn by advancing the queenside majority versus White trying to create a passed pawn on the kingside. }
