16. Rac1 a5 17. b3 Bf7
{ Threatening to take on c3 and then win back the pawn on e2. } 18. Rfe1 Nxc3
19. Rxc3 Kf6 20. e3
{ Note that White cannot play  20.Nd4  yet because Black can simply take the knight with  20...Rxd4  . }
20... g5 21. Rec1 f4
{ Black has sufficient compensation with the active pieces @@StartBracket@@the knight can jump to d3, the rooks can enter either on e2 or d2, the bishop can go to h5@@EndBracket@@ and White's extra pawn is not going anywhere. }
