16. Be4 Rxf4 17. Bxf4 Bh3 18. Re1 Qf7
{ Black has only a minor weakness on e7 that is easy to defend while White has no knight to land on e6. Black was able to make a draw comfortably in the game Mauro-Polsterer, ICCF email 2017. }
