10... fxe4 11. Nxe4 Nxe4 12. Bxe4 c6
{ The idea of this move is not only to play ...Nc7 @@StartBracket@@c5@@EndBracket@@ followed by ...e7-e5 @@StartBracket@@when sometimes the d6-pawn turns out to be weak@@EndBracket@@, but also simply attacking the pawn on d5, followed by ...Nc7 and ...Qf7 to increase the pressure. }
13. Bg2 Nc7 14. a4
{ Black sometimes takes on d5 and then plays ...Nb5 to reduce the pressure and find good squares for the pieces. The move a2-a4 prevents this plan. }
14... cxd5 15. cxd5 a5
{ Taking control over the b4-square so that a black knight on c5 cannot be hit by b2-b4. }
16. Bg5 Qf7 { The pawn d5 hangs. } 17. Ne2 Na6
{ White has put his knight on the passive square e2 while Black can choose to play ...Nb4 or ...Nc5 at some point. The position is about equal as Black has sufficient pressure. }
