{ Taking back with the pawn on e4 is almost never an option.  13...fxe4  14.Ne6  Bxe6  15.dxe6  and  White can defend the e6-pawn with Bh3. }
14. dxc6 bxc6 15. Nf3 Bxb2 16. Rxb2 Qf7
{ Black's position is fine. Because we haven't rushed with ...e7-e5, the pawn on d6 is still well protected. For White, it is not so easy to get b4-b5 in yet because the pawn on c4 would become weak and Black can also consider playing ...a7-a5 and even ...a5-a4 at some point. }
