14. Qa3 { Now the queen can return to c2 via a4. } 14... Nc7
{ Centralizing the pieces − ...Ncd5 is a serious option now followed by ...f5-f4 at some point. }
15. Bd4 Re7 16. e3 a5
{ Black's position is fine, we can expand on the queenside with ...b7-b5, protect the weak c6-pawn by putting a knight on d5, but we can also take less risk and place a knight on e4 and start exchanging some pieces. }
