17. Bg2
{ If White tries to win the knight with  17.b4  , a surprise is reserved in return.  17...Nxc4  followed by ...d6-d5, winning back the material. }
17... c5 { Opening the long diagonal for the g7-bishop. } 18. Qd2 cxd4 19. Bxd4
Bxd4 20. Qxd4 Bf3
{ And we have reached an equal position. Black's only minor weakness, the pawn on e7, is compensated by the weak c4-pawn and the offside knight on a3. }
