12. Ne6 Bxe6 13. dxe6 Rb8 { Just in time to defend the b7-pawn. } 14. a4
{ This is a suggestion from the engine, but Black's play is the same: take control over the light squares and hope to win the pawn on e6. }
14... c6 15. a5 { White is trying to create weaknesses on Black's queenside. }
15... Qc8 16. Be3 b6
{ Black has defended everything and is ready to increase the pressure on the white position with, for example, ...Ng4. }
