{ 6...d5  is atransposition to the lines with 5.b4 and 6.O-O. } 7. a3 d6
{ Black plays for the standard plan of pushing ...e7-e5, making use of possible pins on either the rook on a1 or the bishop on b2, if White takes on e5. }
8. Bb2 e5 9. d5
{ White transposed to a King's Indian type of position, but one where Black has no issues. }
9... Ne7 10. c4 h6
{ Just like in the King's Indian, White plays on the queenside, Black advances on the kingside. }
11. Nc3 g5
{ Compared to a King's Indian, it feels like Black is a lot faster. We can consider playing ...Qe8-h5 followed by ...e5-e4 or ...g5-g4 in combination with ...f5-f4. }
