{ In the King's Indian, Black players dream of such an active bishop, normally it is grounded on c8. }
14. Qb3 Ng6
{ Black has already a dangerous initiative. We can follow up with ...Qd7 and ...Bh3, there are ideas with ...g5-g4 or even ...h6-h5-h4. White needs a lot of time to create something on the c-file where Black can defend by playing ...Rf7. }
