7. O-O c6 { Preparing ...d7-d5. } 8. Bb2 d5 9. Nbd2 Be6
{ The bishop has a good spot on e6 but only after Black has played Ne4 so that there is no annoying Ng5 from White. }
10. cxd5 { This is a typical move that White can play at different moments. }
10... Bxd5
