{ Considering White has already a pawn on c4, the focus is on getting d4-d5 in. }
7... d6 8. d5 Ne5 { There was no need to go back passively to b8. } 9. Nxe5
dxe5 10. Bb2
{ White wants to prove that Black's double e-pawns are not useful and the space advantage on the queenside is important, but the engine shows there are no big problems for Black. }
10... e4 11. Nc3 e6 { Fixing Black's structure. } 12. Qb3 exd5 13. Nxd5 Be6
{ All pieces are developed and there is a pawn on e4 already. } 14. Rd1 Nxd5
{ Getting rid of the annoying knight on d5 and clarifying the complications. }
15. cxd5 Bf7 16. Bxg7 Kxg7 17. O-O Qf6
{ The position is equal. White's pawn on d5 can become weak but Black's pawn on c7 is not great either. For now, Black has a nice pawn on e4, but that might be traded soon if White plays f2-f3. }
