8. a4 { 8.Qa4  is not dangerous, Black simply defends with  8...b6  . } 8...
Ne4 { The idea of this move is to gain space and prepare e7-e5. } 9. Nxe4 fxe4
10. f3 e5 { Black is always happy to get this pawn break in. } 11. Nh3 exd4 12.
cxd4 exf3 13. exf3 Qe7+ 14. Kf2 O-O
{ A dangerous exchange sacrifice that according to the engine gives Black a clear advantage. }
15. Ba3 Qf6 16. Bxf8 Kxf8
{ Black at least wins the pawn on d4, so with a pawn for the exchange the material deficit is minimal and the black pawns on the queenside are ready to move forward. }
