7... e5
{ The direct pawn push is also possible but the resulting position is a bit boring. }
8. b3 Nc6 9. dxe5 dxe5
{ Taking with the knight on e5 is suboptimal because the white knight can come to f4 and there is some pressure against the pawn on b7. }
10. Ba3 Re8 11. Qxd8 Nxd8 12. Nd5
{ White is trying to create play over the c-file. } 12... Nxd5 13. cxd5 Bd7
{ Black is in time to defend c7. } 14. Rac1 Rc8
{ There is nothing wrong with Black's position, but playing for a win will not be easy. White may double rooks on the c-file and Black probably starts by playing ...Bf8 and then ...c7-c6. Because of first playing ...Bf8, it is less attractive for White to play d5-d6 and if White doesn't double on the c-file, Black may play ...Nf7-d6 and leave the pawn on c7 for the time being. }
