8. exf5 { White continues to put pressure on the light squares. } 8... exf5 9.
O-O Nc6
{ The plan with ...b7-b6 followed by ...c7-c5 might be playable, it just seems a bit slow here. }
10. c3 { Trying to limit the power of the f6-bishop. } 10... Qd6
{ First developing the queen and then the bishop to d7. } 11. Bc2
{ White wants to regroup the minor pieces: one knight on d3 and the other on f3, to take control over the e5-square. }
11... Bd7 12. Ne1 Rae8
{ Sooner or later both sides will have a rook on the e-file. } 13. Nd3 Nd8
{ Rerouting the knight to f7 where it still controls the e5-square but also enables ...g7-g5 and ...b7-b6, followed by ...c7-c5. }
14. Nf3 Nf7
{ The position is equal. It is likely all the rooks will be exchanged on the e-file and both sides have solid pawn structures without any major weaknesses, so it will be difficult to avoid a draw. }
