{ If we don't attack that bishop quickly, Black might get in trouble on the light squares as White would play Rf1 @@StartBracket@@or short castle@@EndBracket@@. }
10. Bb3 Nxb3 11. axb3 Bg7 12. O-O Bf5 13. Qd2 O-O
{ I feel Black has every reason here to be optimistic with an extra pawn and a pair of bishops. The engine still thinks it is within the margin of equality, but luckily in practice, we play against humans! }
