10... Bxc6 11. a3
{ White wants to increase the pressure on the e4-pawn by getting rid of the pin on the c3-knight, but it is at the expense of the king's safety. }
11... Ba5 12. b4 Bb6
{ Two beautiful bishops, therefore I would always prefer Black in this position. }
13. fxe4 fxe4 14. Ng3 Qd7
{ White might be able to win the e4-pawn back, but Black is likely to end up on top with the pair of bishops and the pressure against the pawn on d4 after queenside castling. }
