Rc1 Nxf3+ 13. Bxf3 a5
{ It is important to stop White's plan of queenside expansion with b2-b4. } 14.
Qd3 e5 15. dxe6 c6
{ White can now try to win the pawn on d6, but Black is just in time. } 16.
Rfd1 Bxe6 { Attacking the pawn on c4. } 17. b3 Be5
