{ Black cannot do without this move if we want to castle kingside. } 6. O-O Bg7
7. Nbd2 O-O 8. h3 Nc6 9. c3
{ White is playing it solidly, but this is precisely when it becomes easy to play the Leningrad: prepare to play the e7-pawn @@StartBracket@@via e6 in this case@@EndBracket@@ to e5. }
