[Black "English Setups − 1.Nf3 with 5.c4 #4"]
[Result "*"]

1. Nf3 f5 2. g3 Nf6 3. Bg2 g6 4. O-O Bg7 5. c4
{ We have transposed to an English opening that could also have started with 1.c4. Also, at any point, White can decide to play d2-d4 and transpose to a main line of the Leningrad System. }
5... O-O 6. Nc3 d6 7. d3
{ This was White's final chance to make it a 1.d4 opening. } 7... Nc6
{ In all these English lines I like the knight on c6. Placing the knight on a6 is less logical in these types of positions because after the knight moves to c5 there is a pawn on d3 preventing a future knight jump to e4. }
8. Rb1 a5
{ Black can also play without the inclusion of ...a7-a5 and a2-a3, but I feel that opening the a-file benefits Black. }
9. a3 Nh5
{ The pawn push b2-b4 is not working because the knight on c3 would be hanging, thus Black is preparing ...f5-f4. }
10. d4
{ A rarely played move but dangerous. Luckily, most English players don't like to put this pawn on d4 in one go, they like to lose a tempo with d2-d3! }
10... f4 { The main idea behind playing ...Nh5. } 11. b4 axb4 12. axb4 e5
{ Black has to occupy the center at some point and this seems to be the right timing, there are no other obvious moves that work well. }
13. d5 { This is also an obvious move we need to study. } 13... Nd4 14. Nxd4
exd4 15. Nb5 Bf5 16. Rb3 Ra1 17. Qd2 { 17.Nxd4  runs into  17...Rxc1  . } 17...
d3
{ Much stronger than allowing White to take with the knight on d4. Now White's pawn structure gets disrupted. }
18. exd3
{ White's extra pawn is on d3, which means it is hardly an extra pawn, while Black is quite active. }
18... Qd7 19. Bb2 Ra2
{ This is a nice pin on the second rank. For the time being, White cannot move the b3-rook. }
20. d4 Bh6
{ Although this bishop is not protected, Black has a clear idea in mind. } 21.
f3 fxg3 { A temporary piece sacrifice. } 22. Qxh6 Bc2
{ That was Black's idea. } 23. Rc3 gxh2+ 24. Kxh2 Rxb2
{ With chances for both sides according to the engine, but I prefer Black with the safer king and the possibility to put a knight on f4. }
