{ A good square for the knight. If White plays e2-e3 the knight will be happy to go to f5. }
18. Bg5 Qf8
{ Black has a fine position. The white pawns on e2 and b2 can easily be attacked, the a-file may be open if White plays b2-b4, and the pawn on h5 may not be great, but there is no way for White to attack it. }
