10... Bg4 11. h3 Bh5 12. O-O Na6 13. Qe2
{ It is not easy for White to resolve the pin on the f3-knight. On  13.Qd3  Black will play  13...Nc5  followed by ...Qd7 and the pawns on h3 and e4 are weak. }
