[Black "Nimzo-Larsen 1.b3 f5 − Dutch-style #18"]
[Result "*"]

1. b3 f5 { If we can play this on the first move, we will! } 2. Bb2 Nf6
{ There is no reason to be afraid of Bxf6 in this position. Black would take back with the e-pawn, play ...d7-d5 next, and develop in the same way as in the 2.Nc3 line: ...Be6, ...Nc6, ...Qd7 and castle queenside. }
3. e3 e6
{ 3...d6  4.d4  e6  would be transposition to the main line,  but why would we give White the additional opportunity to take on f6 on move 4 when Black probably needs to lose a tempo later to play ...d6-d5? }
4. f4 { Both sides can keep the symmetry for a long time. } 4... b6
{ Clearly the c8-bishop has a future on b7. } 5. Nf3 Bb7 6. g3
{ White continues with the symmetry. } 6... g6 { And Black copies White. } 7.
Bg2 Bg7 8. O-O O-O 9. d3 d6 { Both sides continue with symmetrical play. } 10.
Nbd2 Nbd7 11. Qe2
{ And now the first deviation from copying each other comes. } 11... Re8
{ Both sides have completed their development. If White pushes the e-pawn now, it will get lost. }
12. Rae1 c5
{ Before playing ...e6-e5, Black wants to weaken the pawn on d3. Of course, there are other moves, such as  12...Qe7  , with which Black can also maintain the balance. }
13. c4 e5 { Black is trying to bring some excitement to the game. } 14. fxe5
{ Had White continued the symmetry by playing  14.e4  , the position would have been nearly lost after Black's  14...exf4  . }
14... Nxe5
{ Black takes with the knight so that after White exchanges one more time on e5 the black queen eyes the pawn on d3. }
15. Nxe5 Bxg2 16. Qxg2 dxe5
{ The pawn on d3 hangs and if White defends it with  17.Qe2  and refuses to play e3-e4 at some point, the position could easily drift to passivity. }
17. e4 f4
{ Black sacrifices a pawn in a way that is similar to some of the main lines in the Leningrad System. }
18. gxf4 Nh5 19. Bxe5 Bxe5 20. fxe5 Qxd3
{ White is a pawn up, but Black has sufficient compensation. Both White's e-pawns are potentially weak and the knight on h5 is happy to go to f4. In a practical game, this is a good way for Black to unbalance the position and play for a win. }
