[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "20. Model Games"]
[Black "Josep Oms Pallisse vs. Karen Movsziszian, La Pobla de Lillet 1997"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 f5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Bg5
{ White plays a rare system with first Nf3 and then Bg5. } 3... e6
{ Note that Black doesn't want to allow a double pawn on the f-file. That can be done in the line with 2.Nc3 because the knight blocks the c2-pawn and it will give Black sufficient time to take control over the light squares with ...d7-d5. Here, White would take on f6 followed by playing c2-c4 and Black doesn't have sufficient compensation for the doubled f-pawns. }
4. Nbd2 Be7 5. Bxf6 Bxf6
{ Whether the bishop is on g7 or on f6, it still feels like a Leningrad bishop. White took on f6 because he wants to take control over the light squares after e2-e4. }
6. e4 O-O 7. c3 d5 { Black is fighting for the light squares. } 8. exf5
{ White could also have played e4-e5, after which the bishop drops back to e7 followed by ...c7-c5. }
8... exf5 9. Bd3 Re8+ 10. Kf1
{ White has lost the right to castle but it is not a big deal because his king is safe and will soon move to g2. }
10... b6 { Preparing ...c7-c5. } 11. g3 c5 12. Kg2 Nc6
{ Putting pressure on the d4-pawn. } 13. Bb5 Bb7 14. Nf1 Re4
{ Black continues to activate his pieces and attack the pawn on d4. } 15. Ne3
f4
{ Black could have improved with  15...cxd4  16.Bxc6  Bxc6  17.Nxd4  Bxd4  18.cxd4  Qf6  and White probably needs to play  19.Nc2  , but after  19...Rae8  Black has a clear advantage. }
16. Ng4 fxg3 17. Nxf6+ Qxf6 18. hxg3 Rf8
{ White has a serious problem on the f-file. } 19. Rf1 Ne7
{ Bringing more pieces to help with the kingside attack. } 20. Ne5
{ 20.Bd3  was the only move for White, now he is lost. } 20... Nf5 21. Bd3
{ Going for material gains won't be good for White either, his king is helpless against the black pieces:  21.Nd7  Nh4+  and mate is not far away in all the lines.  22.gxh4   22.Kh2  Qh6  23.Kg1  Nf3+  and Black wins a queen.  22...Qg6+  23.Kh3  Rff4  and the engine says mate in 6. }
21... Rxe5
{ Of course, Black wants to open the long diagonal for the b7-bishop. } 22.
dxe5 d4+ 23. Kg1 Qh6
{ White resigned, the queen is coming to h1 and the only way to prevent this,  24.f3  fails simply to  24...Nxg3  . Another quick attacking victory for Black. Already on move 15 he had a nice advantage and the attack didn't require anything special, Black almost won on autopilot. }
