{ Distracting the knight on c2 from defending the white king. } 21. Nxb4 Rxf2
{ Threatening ...Qxe3+ and mate on d2. } 22. Kxf2
{ 22.Qb3  Rxb4  23.Qxd5+  Rf7  24.Qxe4  Rb2  and Black has a winning attack in all the lines with the two rooks and queen. }
22... Rf8+ 23. Ke2 Qg2+ { White loses both rooks. } 24. Kd1 Qxh1+ 25. Kc2 Qxa1
{ White's position is hopeless, Black is up in material and still has a dangerous attack. }
